📘 Subject: General Studies Paper I (Prelims – Polity)
🧠 Topic: Prime Minister & Council of Ministers

(One of the MOST important topics in Polity.)

1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Who is the Prime Minister?

The Prime Minister (PM) is:

Real executive head of India
Leader of the government
Head of Council of Ministers

📌 Mentioned in Articles 74–75

🔵 Appointment of Prime Minister
Appointed by the President
Usually the leader of majority party in Lok Sabha

📌 If no clear majority → coalition leader appointed.

🔹 Council of Ministers

Includes:

1️⃣ Cabinet Ministers
2️⃣ Ministers of State
3️⃣ Deputy Ministers

📌 PM is the head of this council.

🔴 Collective Responsibility
Council of Ministers is collectively responsible to Lok Sabha

👉 If Lok Sabha passes no-confidence motion, entire council resigns.

📌 Very important concept.

🔹 Powers of Prime Minister
1️⃣ Executive Powers
Appoints ministers
Allocates portfolios
Controls administration
2️⃣ Legislative Powers
Leader of Lok Sabha
Advises President on Parliament sessions
3️⃣ Financial Powers
Plays key role in budget
Economic decision-making
4️⃣ Diplomatic Powers
Represents India internationally
Foreign policy decisions
🔹 Relationship with President
President acts on advice of PM
PM is the link between President & Council of Ministers

📌 Article 74 → Advice binding.

🔹 Important Points
PM must be member of Parliament
If not, must become MP within 6 months
Real power lies with PM in parliamentary system
